<div id="pf5" class="pf w0 h4" data-page-no="5"><div class="pc pc5 w0 h4"><img class="bi x0 y0 w1 h5" alt="" src="bg5.png"/><div class="t m7b xf h14 y77 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">From Homer A. Kent, </div><div class="t m7c x31 h14 y78 ff5 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Pastoral Epistles, </div><div class="t m7d x32 h14 y78 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 50. </div><div class="t m7e x33 h15 y79 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Introduction to 1 Timothy and Titus </div><div class="t m7f x13 h14 y7a ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Our lessons this quarter are based on the letters of the apostle </div><div class="t m80 x33 h14 y7b ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Paul to two young ministers and missionaries—Timothy and </div><div class="t m81 x33 h14 y7c ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Titus. Written against the backdrop of the first-century Chris-</div><div class="t m82 x33 h14 y7d ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tian church, these letters contain admonitions and guidelines </div><div class="t m83 x33 h14 y7e ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that are timeless. They speak to </div><div class="t m84 x34 h14 y7e ff5 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">all </div><div class="t m85 x35 h14 y7e ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">who carry responsibility in </div><div class="t m86 x33 h14 y7f ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the church—every follower of Christ. Because we are a royal </div><div class="t m46 x33 h14 y80 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">priesthood (1 Peter 2:9), every believer is called to contribute to </div><div class="t m87 x33 h14 y81 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the life of the church and to fulfill Christ&apos;s mission in the world. </div><div class="t m88 x36 h16 y82 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">OUTLINE OF 1 TIMOTHY </div><div class="t m89 xa h14 y83 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">I. </div><div class="t m25 x37 h14 y83 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Salutation, 1:1, 2. </div><div class="t m8a x9 h14 y84 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">II. </div><div class="t m8b x37 h14 y85 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Charge to Rebuke False Teachers, 1:3-20. </div><div class="t m42 x11 h14 y86 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">III. </div><div class="t m65 x37 h14 y87 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Universality of Christian Worship, 2:1-15. </div><div class="t m7b x11 h14 y88 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">IV. </div><div class="t m59 x37 h14 y89 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Prerequisites for Christian Leaders, 3:1-13. </div><div class="t m8c x9 h14 y8a ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">V. </div><div class="t m8d x37 h14 y8b ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Christian Message, 3:14 to 4:5. </div><div class="t m8e x11 h14 y8c ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">VI. </div><div class="t m8f x37 h14 y8c ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Practical Counsel for Ministers, 4:6-16. </div><div class="t m90 xb h14 y8d ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">VII. </div><div class="t m91 x37 h14 y8e ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Minister as Church Administrator, 5:1 to 6:19. </div><div class="t m92 x38 h14 y8f ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">VIII. </div><div class="t m93 x39 h14 y8f ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Paul&apos;s Final Charge to Timothy, 6:20, 21. </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
